PROFILE SUMMARY  
Senior Programme Quality and MEAL professional with 12+ years of experience leading monitoring, evaluation, accountability, learning, 
adaptive management, and programme quality systems across humanitarian, resilience, and development programmes in the MENA 
region. Proven experience supporting multi-sector and multi-partner portfolios funded by FCDO, USAID, EU, OCHA, DFID, BMZ, 
UNICEF, and WFP across complex emergency settings. 
Experienced in consortium coordination, strategic planning, donor compliance, evaluations, accountability systems, evidence generation, 
and cross-functional programme leadership. Extensive experience collaborating with INGOs, UN agencies, consortium partners, and local 
organizations including CARE International, Relief International, WFP, FAO, DRC, and the Lebanese Red Cross to strengthen programme 
quality, accountability, adaptive management, and evidence-based decision-making. 
